claim.claim-text:
A membrane based desalination method comprising:
achieving a first solution from salinity water source;
pressurizing the first solution in a first pressure exchange device;
separating the first solution into a second solution and a third solution;
pressurizing the second solution;
pressurizing the third solution in a second pressure exchange device;
mixing the second solution and the third solution as a fourth solution;
providing the fourth solution to a first semi-permeable membrane to achieve product water;
providing a fifth solution, which is the fourth solution excluding the product water, to the second pressure exchange device for pressurizing the third solution;
providing the fifth solution to a second semi-permeable membrane after pressurizing the third solution;
achieving a sixth solution which has lower salinity than the fifth solution; and
providing the sixth solution to the second semi-permeable membrane for drawing water from the sixth solution to the fifth solution by salinity gradient,
wherein after drawing water from the sixth solution to the fifth solution, the fifth solution is given to the first pressure exchange device for pressurizing the first solution.

A membrane based desalination method comprising:
achieving inlet solution from high salinity solution;
providing the inlet solution to the first semi-permeable membrane for achieving product water;
providing draw solution, which is extracted from the first semi-permeable membrane, to the second semi-permeable membrane; and
providing feed solution, which has lower salinity than the draw solution, to the second semi-permeable membrane for drawing water from the feed solution to the draw solution by salinity gradient,
wherein the inlet solution is given to pressure exchange device before being provided to the first semi-permeable membrane, and the draw solution is given to the pressure exchange device after being provided to the second semi-permeable membrane for pressurizing the inlet solution.

A membrane based desalination apparatus comprising:
inlet solution storing chamber for storing inlet solution which is salinity water;
the first pressure exchange device for pressurizing the inlet solution;
the second pressure exchange device for further pressurizing the inlet solution which is pressurized by the first pressure exchange device;
the first osmosis chamber including the first semi-permeable membrane, wherein the inlet solution pressurized in the first pressure exchange device and the second pressure exchange device, is separated into product water and draw solution by reversed osmotic process;
feed solution storing chamber for storing feed solution which has lower salinity than the draw solution; and
the second osmosis chamber including the second semi-permeable membrane, wherein the feed solution and the draw solution are given to the second osmosis chamber, wherein water is drawn from the feed solution to the draw solution;
wherein the second pressure exchange device pressurizes the inlet solution by transferring pressure of the draw solution, and
wherein the first pressure exchange device pressurizes the inlet solution by transferring pressure of solution discharged from the second osmosis chamber.
